 the market.Both studies include Japan, China, Hong Kong, Taiwan, Singapore, Korea, Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand and Philippines. Both also consider the implications of taxation for savings and investment flows in domestic economies and across borders-and the implications of public sector demand for savings for corporate financing constraints.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aFinancezEast Asia. 0aFinancial criseszEast Asia. 0aTaxationzEast Asia. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Finance / General.2bisacsh1 aAivazian, Varouj A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBird, Richard M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Duanjie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobson, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobson, Wendy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHan, J.D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHejazi, Walid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144267490540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442674905423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442674905.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  a978-3-11-064968-0  Asian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Package  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  